- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a framework for model checking parameterized transition systems, which is a topic closely related to logic in computer science.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with weak memory models, which are relevant to programming languages and their implementation.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper presents a tool for model checking, which is a software engineering technique.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with transition systems, which are a topic in formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with array-based transition systems, which are related to data structures.
